<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Sun, 28 Jun 2026 13:12:24 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>中国在网络安全领域与人类不相上下，重新启动人工智能竞赛</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/china-has-matched-anthropic-in-cybersecurity-resetting-ai-race</link><description>对美国顶级人工智能的打压加剧了人们对华盛顿正在让北京获得网络战优势的担忧。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/china-has-matched-anthropic-in-cybersecurity-resetting-ai-race.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 28 Jun 2026 13:12:22 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/china-has-matched-anthropic-in-cybersecurity-resetting-ai-race</guid></item><item><title>真正的人工智能竞赛不是美国与中国的较量</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/the-real-a-i-race-isnt-america-vs-china</link><description>在人工智能政策方面，华盛顿开始遵循与北京类似的策略。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-real-a-i-race-isnt-america-vs-china.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 28 Jun 2026 12:57:22 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/the-real-a-i-race-isnt-america-vs-china</guid></item><item><title>科学家发现了降低结直肠癌风险的基因“盾牌”</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/scientists-uncover-a-genetic-shield-that-lowers-the-risk-of-colorectal-cancer</link><description>来自芭芭拉·安·卡马诺斯癌症研究所、韦恩州立大学和美国各地机构的一组科学家发表了一篇关于癌症作用的新论文&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/scientists-uncover-a-genetic-shield-that-lowers-the-risk-of-colorectal-cancer.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 28 Jun 2026 12:42:22 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/scientists-uncover-a-genetic-shield-that-lowers-the-risk-of-colorectal-cancer</guid></item><item><title>患有创伤后应激障碍 (PTSD) 的 WTC 响应者与衰老速度加快和慢性疾病有关</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/faster-aging-chronic-disease-linked-to-wtc-responders-with-ptsd</link><description>双子塔袭击事件发生 25 年后，创伤后应激障碍 (PTSD) 仍然是影响世贸中心 (WTC) 救援人员的常见病症。虽然这种情况被认为主要是心理疾病，但一项新的研究揭示了患有 PTSD 的世贸中心患者的生物过程的变化，这可能解释了为什么 PTSD 与多种最终导致衰老的慢性疾病有关。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/faster-aging-chronic-disease-linked-to-wtc-responders-with-ptsd.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 28 Jun 2026 12:27:22 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/faster-aging-chronic-disease-linked-to-wtc-responders-with-ptsd</guid></item><item><title>更好的心脏“数字双胞胎”可以帮助房颤的针对性治疗</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/better-heart-digital-twins-could-help-target-treatment-for-atrial-fibrillation</link><description>由伦敦玛丽女王大学研究人员领导的跨大学论文，发表在&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/better-heart-digital-twins-could-help-target-treatment-for-atrial-fibrillation.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 28 Jun 2026 12:12:22 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/better-heart-digital-twins-could-help-target-treatment-for-atrial-fibrillation</guid></item><item><title>新技术有助于揭示心脏如何产生具有再生潜力的细胞</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/new-technology-helps-reveal-how-the-heart-generates-cells-with-regenerative-potential</link><description>卡洛斯三世国家心血管研究中心 (CNIC) 的两个研究小组在西班牙开发了一项开创性技术，用于表征单个心肌细胞（负责心脏收缩的细胞）的蛋白质组。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/new-technology-helps-reveal-how-the-heart-generates-cells-with-regenerative-potential2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 28 Jun 2026 11:57:22 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/new-technology-helps-reveal-how-the-heart-generates-cells-with-regenerative-potential</guid></item><item><title>受量子启发的人工智能可以根据患者的整个分子背景定制癌症治疗</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/quantum-inspired-ai-could-tailor-patients-cancer-treatment-to-their-entire-molecular-background</link><description>对于被诊断患有神经母细胞瘤（最常见的婴儿癌症，当早期神经细胞生长失控时发生）的儿童来说，治疗之路并不简单。某些类型的神经母细胞瘤会自行消退，而另一些则需要积极干预。研究人员尝试根据单基因突变对患者进行匹配治疗，但成效有限。这是因为患者的治疗结果取决于他们的整个分子背景，其中包含数百万甚至数十亿的特征，例如来自组织和血液的 DNA 和 RNA。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/quantum-inspired-ai-could-tailor-patients-cancer-treatment-to-their-entire-molecular-background.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 28 Jun 2026 11:42:22 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/quantum-inspired-ai-could-tailor-patients-cancer-treatment-to-their-entire-molecular-background</guid></item><item><title>细胞内机制促进缺氧期间肿瘤的存活</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/intracellular-mechanisms-promote-tumor-survival-during-hypoxia</link><description>根据最近的一项研究，西北医学科学家首次描述了调节细胞如何快速改变基因表达以应对缺氧的潜在机制，缺氧是许多难治性肿瘤的一个关键特征&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/intracellular-mechanisms-promote-tumor-survival-during-hypoxia.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 28 Jun 2026 11:27:22 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/intracellular-mechanisms-promote-tumor-survival-during-hypoxia</guid></item><item><title>美国模式将桥梁材料使用量减少 90%，打造绿色建筑</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/us-model-cuts-bridge-material-use-by-90-unlocks-greener-buildings</link><description>麻省理工学院的研究人员刚刚推出了一种新的计算机方法，可以帮助建造桥梁时减少 90% 的材料。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/us-model-cuts-bridge-material-use-by-90-unlocks-greener-buildings.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 28 Jun 2026 11:12:22 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/us-model-cuts-bridge-material-use-by-90-unlocks-greener-buildings</guid></item><item><title>FTC 批准马斯克收购 SpaceX 校友初创公司 Mesh</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/ftc-gives-musk-the-ok-to-acquire-spacex-alumni-startup-mesh</link><description>Mesh Optical 在二月份宣布筹集资金后不再隐秘。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/ftc-gives-musk-the-ok-to-acquire-spacex-alumni-startup-mesh.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 28 Jun 2026 10:57:22 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/ftc-gives-musk-the-ok-to-acquire-spacex-alumni-startup-mesh</guid></item></channel></rss>